        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>270. Lextn. St.<lb/>
                Balto. July 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 81.<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd. S. Morais<lb/>
                Phila.<lb/>
                My Dear Pastor.<lb/></p>
            <p>You must accept my<lb/> sincere &#38; grateful <sic>acknowlegements</sic><lb/> for your very kind note&#44; received<lb/> this morning&#44; expressing such<lb/> gratifying solicitude for my health&#44;<lb/> &#38; expressions of sympathy in my<lb/> latest &#38; deepest affliction.  Your<lb/> letter found me <hi rend="underline">still</hi> in my<lb/> &#34;old house&#34; now&#44; so very desolate.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>You who have experienced such<lb/> a bereavement can fully under<lb/>stand the sad void it creates in<lb/> ones heart &#38; life.  I trust I<lb/> may &#40;thro. Gods grace &#38; mercy&#41; be<lb/> supported to fulfill his dearest<lb/> wish for me&#44; a useful &#38; peaceful<lb/> <sic>existance</sic> on earth as a fitting<lb/> preparation to rejoin her in the<lb/> &#34;holy &#91;&#63;&#93; that waits a life well<lb/> spent.&#34;  My health is good&#45;&#45;<lb/>&#45;&#45;thanks&#33;  &#38; you will see me<lb/> &#40;if nothing prevents&#41; occupy my<lb/> seat in our &#34;House of Prayer&#34;<lb/> on the approaching New Year.<lb/>  I should have announced this<lb/> word to you&#8212;but neglected to<lb/> do so&#33;  Which pray forgive.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Our kind Rabbi&#8212;Revd. H. Hochheimer<lb/> visited my beloved one frequently&#44; &#38; performed<lb/> the last sad services by her request&#45;&#45;&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/>ding&#44; the prayers of each evening of &#34;the Sheva.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>Ask my old schoolmate Mrs Florance&#44;<lb/> to receive my affec&#39;t sympathy&#8212;Believe me<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir  Sincerely &#38; Respty Yrs<lb/>
                J Etting.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Mordecais are at &#34;Chest. Hill&#34; for the summer.<lb/></p>
        </body>
